[start section id="20106"]

Upon interview, the patient confirms the above clinical history. She notes ruefully that, in retrospect, she would have pursued colonoscopy sooner but was attributing her abdominal pain to her known gastroparesis. She had not had a complete colonoscopy since her abdominal catastrophe in 1977.

[end section id="20106"]


